children.text: The overall height of this room is less than the minimum height prescribed by the BCA.
Part 3.8.2.2 Height of rooms and other spaces requirements of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) requires that
‘Heights of rooms and other spaces (see Figure 3.8.2.1) must be not less than;
in a habitable room excluding a kitchen - 2.4m;
in a corridor, passageway or the like - 2.1m;
in a bathroom, shower room, laundry, sanitary compartment, airlock, pantry, storeroom, garage, car parking area or the like - 2.1m,
in a room or space with a sloping ceiling or projections below the ceiling line within a habitable room, a height of not less than 2.4m over two-thirds of the floor area of the room or space;
in a stairway, ramp, landing, or the like - 2.0 m measured vertically above the nosing line of stairway treads or the floor surface of a ramp, landing or the like’
This area will need to be reconstructed so the room height is in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
